<Page title="Affiliate Disclosure" description="Fudgeboop affiliate disclosure — how we earn revenue and maintain editorial independence.">
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 17 March 2026</p>

  <p>
    Fudgeboop is a participant in affiliate marketing programmes. This means that when you click on certain links on our site and make a purchase, we may receive a small commission. <strong>This comes at no additional cost to you.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>How It Works</h2>
  <p>
    Some of the links on fudgeboop.com are "affiliate links". When you click on one of these links and buy a product, the retailer pays us a small referral fee. This is how we keep the site running — we don't run display ads or sell your data.
  </p>

  <h2>Affiliate Programmes We Participate In</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Amazon Associates</strong> — Fudgeboop is a participant in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Programme, an affiliate advertising programme designed to provide a means for sites to earn advertising fees by advertising and linking to Amazon.com and affiliated sites.</li>
    <li><strong>LTK / RewardStyle</strong> — We partner with beauty retailers like Sephora, Ulta, and individual beauty brands through the LTK and RewardStyle affiliate networks.</li>
    <li><strong>Other programmes</strong> — We may participate in additional affiliate programmes. Any affiliate relationship will be disclosed on the relevant post.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our Promise</h2>
  <p>Affiliate commissions do not influence our recommendations. We follow these principles:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>We only recommend products we have researched or tested</li>
    <li>We clearly mark posts that contain affiliate links</li>
    <li>Every affiliate post includes a disclosure notice at the top</li>
    <li>We will tell you if a product has drawbacks, even if it earns us a commission</li>
    <li>We will never recommend a product solely because it has a high commission rate</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>FTC Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    In accordance with the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) guidelines, we disclose that we receive compensation from companies whose products we review and recommend. All opinions expressed on this site are our own.
  </p>
  <p>
    Every blog post containing affiliate links includes a disclosure banner at the top. Pin descriptions that link to affiliate content include the #affiliate hashtag.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions?</h2>
  <p>If you have any questions about our affiliate relationships, contact us at <strong>hello@fudgeboop.com</strong>.</p>
</Page>
